display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> be a non-empty, connected, smooth scheme, with generic point <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\eta ]]></fr:tex>, and let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  X\to  S]]></fr:tex> be an abelian scheme over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>.
    Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H=\operatorname {End}(\mathbb {R}_1f_*\mathbb {Q})]]></fr:tex>, and let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[Z]]></fr:tex> be the centre of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H]]></fr:tex>.
    Suppose that

    
 <html:ol
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
      
 <html:li
style="list-style-type: &quot;(a) &quot;">
        <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X_\eta ]]></fr:tex> is simple over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[k(\eta )]]></fr:tex>.
      </html:li>


      
 <html:li
style="list-style-type: &quot;(b) &quot;">
        <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> does not become constant on any finite covering of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>.
      </html:li>


      
 <html:li
style="list-style-type: &quot;(c) &quot;">
        One of the following conditions is satisfied (cf. <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-ii-4.4.5"
href="hodge-theory-ii-4.4.5.xml"
taxon="Reminder"
number="4.4.5" />):

        
 <html:ol>
          
 <html:li
style="list-style-type: &quot;(1) &quot;">
            <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[Z]]></fr:tex> is imaginary <fr:em>quadratic</fr:em>;
          </html:li>

          
 <html:li
style="list-style-type: &quot;(2) &quot;">
            <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[Z]]></fr:tex> is completely real, and for each real embedding <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\varphi \colon  Z\to \mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex>, <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H\otimes _{Z,\varphi }\mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex> is an algebra of matrices over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex>;
          </html:li>

          
 <html:li
style="list-style-type: &quot;(3) &quot;">
            <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[Z]]></fr:tex> is completely real, and for each real embedding <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\varphi \colon  Z\to \mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex>, <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H\otimes _{Z,\varphi }\mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex> is an algebra of matrices over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {H}]]></fr:tex>.
          </html:li>

        </html:ol>

      </html:li>

    </html:ol></fr:p><fr:p>Then
    <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[       \operatorname {End}(X)       \xrightarrow {\sim } \operatorname {End}(\mathrm {R}_1f_*\mathbb {Z}).     ]]></fr:tex></fr:p>
  
    
